# Cursor rules for atel-sdk
# Single source of truth: https://github.com/AtelLab/atel-team-workspace/blob/main/TEAM-PLAYBOOK.md

## Project facts — DUAL IDENTITY
This repo is BOTH:
1. **npm package `@atel-ai/atel-sdk`** — imported by atel-mcp + atel-portal
2. **prod daemon `atel-agent.service` :3100** — runs on prod box (`atel start <port>`)

Most people only know about (1). Treat (2) as load-bearing.

## Hard rules
- ANY change: `npm publish @atel-ai/atel-sdk` after; check both atel-mcp + atel-portal don't break.
- Backward compatibility is non-negotiable for the npm side. Breaking changes need a major bump + coordinated PRs to all consumers.
- `src/service/server.ts` is the daemon entry — change with care
- `src/gateway/` is the P2P relay link layer — production traffic flows through here
- `src/index.ts` + `bin/atel.mjs` are public entry points — additive only

## Don't touch
- `dist/`, `node_modules/`
- `src/service/server.ts`, `src/gateway/*`, `src/index.ts` API surface — without confirming consumer impact

## Test
- `npm run build` to catch type errors
- `npm test` if tests present
- Manual: run `atel start 3100` locally, hit endpoints

## Recently changed
- DiDi A2B integration removed 2026-05-08 (commit `e09310b`) — may have dead paths
- MCP connector `src/mcp/index.js` added 2026-05-06 — edge cases still being discovered
